content.description: This is a fun route for beginners (toprope).
O My has nice jugs at the start and gets a bit crimpy towards the top with a big move near the end.
content.protection: There is a large, metal rebar at the top for building an anchor off of. You'll need a few pads if you want to boulder the route.

content.description: O Me is slippery at the bottom due to paint. There are nice jugs up top and a strange sloper mantel to finish if you don't use the small tree and traverse left.
content.location: It ascends the left face of the obvious prow on O Wall.

content.description: The alcove at the right end of M Wall has some nice bouldering, but it often tends to be wet. Access to the top can be gained from the right end.L to R:A. Easy Arete, 5.3-4.B. Broken Slab, 5.3.C. Dyno, V0-V2.D. Sweet N Low, unrated (bouldering).E. Sweet N High, unrated (bouldering).O WallTo the right of the gap in the cliff with a view of the Boston Skyline, O Wall rises out of the ground, culminating in a 15 foot arete with good holds. To the right of the O Wall, the cliff shortens abruptly to a few feet and forms the boundary between Granite Railroad Quarry and Swingle's Quarry.A. O Me, V2, 20'.B. O My, 5.6 or V2, 20'.
